                        <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 106.&#8212;<name type="person">Private Daniel Bancroft</name>, <name type="organization">Co. G, 28th Mich.</name>; age 38; admitted <date
                                        type="admit" when="1865-01-28">Jan. 28, 1865</date>. Pain in
                                chest anteriorly; much cough; <choice><orig>sputa</orig><reg>sputum</reg></choice> white, tenacious, abundant;
                                pulse frequent, not hard; much fever at night, with remission in
                                morning.  31st: Pain in left side; dyspn&#339;a; dry cough; hot
                                skin; frequent pulse; physical signs of pleuro-pneumonia.  February
                                3: Pleuritic effusion in left chest, extending to fifth rib in front
                                while sitting.  8th: Erysipelas of face; much dyspn&#339;a;
                                effusion unaltered; delirium.  12th: Failing; left pleura filling up.  <date type="death" when="1865-02-14">14th</date>: Died.   <hi
                                        rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination: Left lower lobe
                                hepatized throughout; a pint of serum and lymph in the pleural
                                cavity and both pleural surfaces covered with coagulable
                                        lymph.&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name type="hospital"
                                                key="189">Third Division Hospital</name>, <name
                                                type="place">Alexandria, Va.</name></hi></p>
